Later on all the Zenke shrines except {{ill|Yomochi Shrine and Ukishima Shrine#Ukishima Shrine|8=ja|9=世持神社|lt=Choju Shrine]] and {{ill|Choraku-ji Tenmangū|en}}
[[ja:長楽寺天満宮|sn|沖宮]] would convert to [[Shingon Buddhism]] and become the {{ill|Eight Ryukyu Shrines|en}}
[[ja:琉球八社]].

Excluded from this list is {{ill|Kin-gū|en}}
[[ja:金武宮]] which although quite small was always affiliated with the [[Shingon Buddhism|Shingon Buddhist]] temple {{ill|Kin Kannon-ji|en}}
[[ja:金武観音寺]] and also joined the {{ill|Eight Ryukyu Shrines|en}}
[[ja:琉球八社]].

