{{Infobox Japanese Temple | Name = Rinkai-ji (臨海寺) | image = [[File:Rinkai-ji.JPG|240px]] | Location = [[:en:Okinawa Prefecture|Okinawa Prefecture]][[:en:Naha|Naha City]][[:en:Akebono|Akebono]] 1-18-19 | Coordinates = {{Coord|26|14|18.9|N|127|40|56.0|E|region:JP-47_scale:10000_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | Mountain Name = {{ill|Okinoshan|ja|沖乃山|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Okinoshan|qq=}} | Temple Name = | Doctrine = | Sect = {{ill|Tōji Shingon Sect|ja|東寺真言宗|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōji Shingon Sect|qq=}} | Principal Image= [[:en:Bhaisajyaguru|Yakushi Nyorai Medicine Buddha]] | Year of Foundation = Unknown | Founder = | Establishment = | Revival Year = | Revival Details= | Formal Name = | Alternate Name = | Pilgrimage = | Cultural Properties = | Official Website = | Official Website Name = }}
'''Rinkai-ji''' (臨海寺, りんかいじ) is a temple of the {{ill|Tōji Shingon Sect|ja|東寺真言宗|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōji Shingon Sect|qq=}} located in [[:en:Okinawa Prefecture|Okinawa Prefecture]], [[:en:Naha|Naha City]].
== History == [[File:琉球八景 臨海潮（湖）聲-Sound of the Lake at Rinkai (Rinkai kosei), from the series Eight Views of the Ryūkyū Islands (Ryūkyū hakkei) MET DP141125.jpg|thumb|200px|Rinkai Kosei (as depicted in a screen painting by [[:en:Hokusai|Katsushika Hokusai]]); a building along the embankment]] The date of its foundation is unknown. The temple is situated along an embankment leading to [[:en:Mie Castle|Mie Castle]], built in the mid-16th century, and once functioned as the bettō (administrative temple) of {{ill|Okimiya|ja|沖宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Okimiya|qq=}}. During the period of the [[:en:Ryukyu Kingdom|Ryukyu Kingdom]], owing to its proximity to {{ill|Naha Port|ja|那覇港|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Naha Port|qq=}}, it served as a temporary lodging facility for foreigners.<ref name="観光">[https://www.naha-contentsdb.jp/spot/555]{{ill|Rinkai-ji|ja|臨海寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rinkai-ji|qq=}} Naha City "Naha City Tourism Resource Database"</ref>
After the separation of Shinto and Buddhism ([[:en:Shinbutsu bunri|Shinbutsu Bunri]]) in the Meiji period, its traditional relationship with Okimiya was severed and the two followed independent paths. The temple suffered catastrophic damage during the [[:en:Battle of Okinawa|Battle of Okinawa]] in 1945 (Showa 20) and was subsequently rebuilt at its current location in the postwar period.<ref name="観光"></ref>
== Access == * A 10‑minute walk from the {{ill|Toshibono Bus Stop|ja|天久停留所|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshibono Bus Stop|qq=}} (local bus).
